---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Us"
  description="Learn about DOGBREEDAGE — the most accurate dog age calculator by breed size. Science-based, veterinarian-approved formulas."
>
  <section class="container-custom py-10 sm:py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-0 sm:px-1">
      <span class="inline-block text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--text-faint)] px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-[var(--border-default)] mb-4 sm:mb-6">About Us</span>
      <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-6 sm:mb-8">About DOGBREEDAGE</h1>
      <div class="space-y-5 sm:space-y-6 text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          DOGBREEDAGE was created to solve a simple problem: dog owners deserve an accurate way to understand their pet's age. The old "multiply by 7" rule is misleading, and most online calculators still use it.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our calculator uses the latest veterinary research — specifically the DNA methylation formula (16 × ln(dog age) + 31) published in the peer-reviewed journal <em>Cell Systems</em> by researchers at UC San Diego. We've enhanced this formula with breed-size multipliers based on extensive lifespan studies.
        </p>
        <p>
          We believe in science-backed pet care. Understanding your dog's true biological age helps you make better decisions about nutrition, exercise, veterinary care, and quality of life at every stage.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our mission is to provide the most accurate, easy-to-use dog age calculator on the web — completely free, with no data collection, and no hidden agendas.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
